<section xml:id="sec_opt-app-challenge" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Challenge - Optical Applications</title>
	
	<!--
	If you want an A*R*C*S (Analyze-Represent-Calculate-Sensemake) activity, use the <project> tag.
	If you want an Explain activity, use the <investigation> tag.
		Use this text for qualitative comparisons: <em>greater than</em>, <em>less than</em>, or <em>equal to</em>
	If you want a Calculate activity, use the <problem> tag.  (This tag is Example-like, not Project-like, so you cannot embed lettered steps into it using <task>.
	-->

	<subsubsection>
	<title>Explanation Task</title>
		</subsubsection>



		<subsubsection>
	<title>A*R*C*S Activities</title>
	</subsubsection>

	<project xml:id="pa_opt-10">
		<title>Intensity on the Screen</title>
		<statement>
			<p></p> 
			<p>
				You have a laser with wavelength <m>\lambda = 550 \mathrm{~nm}</m>.  You shine this laser through the mask with two slits shown below, where <m>s = 0.5 \mathrm{~mm}</m>.  Create and label a diagram of the pattern that appears on a screen that has been placed a distance <m>L = 2.0 \mathrm{~m}</m> away from the mask.  The location of bright and dark spots should be quantitatively accurate; the relative intensity should be qualitatively accurate.  Your diagram should include many bright and dark spots (enough to see all the interesting parts of the pattern), and you should include additional diagrams alongside your sensemaking.

			</p>
			<figure>
			<title>Mask with Two Slits</title>
            <caption>A mask with two slits.</caption>
            <image source="Masks.png" width = "75%"><description></description></image>
          </figure>
		</statement>
	</project>

		

	<subsubsection>
		<title>Metacognitive Reflection</title>
		</subsubsection>

</section>

